<td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> LVL 24 wiz sick of killing birds</span><hr size=1> hi, im a lvl 24 wiz. im looking for another place to solo. I've camping the one spawn in LR too long, its mostly green now, with very xp. I don't mind grouping, just don't like to group with people that don't understand what OOM or NOT READY means and pull 3 or 4 yellow or red mods. I have jboots so im looking for a little fun <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I've been told LOIO is good for grouping. just need to know am I stuck with grouping now?<br>
<br>
costlyfyre lvl 24<br>
zeb server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/27/01 11:59:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LVL 24 wiz sick of killing birds</span><hr size=1> I'm 25 on Saryrn and have had a really hard time finding solo-able MOBs outside of LR myself, cause of problems with root and Enstill.   But I have good news: I found that Fire elementals in Lavastorm and Erud's Crossing are REALLY easy to root, they con blue to me at 24 and 25, and they give pretty good XP.  They're tougher to find in Erud's crossing, but not nearly as tough in lavastorm.<br>
<br>
If anyone else has any ideas for solo spots at this level range, I'd love to hear them too. <p><br>Aniar Orrenson
<br>Wizard of the 25th Season
<br>High Councilman of the Nightwatch of Norrath</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cumdar>Cumdar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/28/01 9:56:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LVL 24 wiz sick of killing birds</span><hr size=1> I'm at 26 now.  I've done 5 levels (mostly grouping in Ill Omen) in about a 2 weeks of playing about 6 hours a week.  The XP is really good if you get in a good group.  And most of the groups I have heard the tanks say &quot;casters go ahead and med&quot; when they knew we were low on mana.  I have solo'ed sarnacks and goblins there but it takes pretty much a full bar of mana to do it.  Loot is ok, but you get lots of runes of the appropriate levels if your into research.  Getting groups can be tough in the beginning but now I am getting a rep as a good wizzy and when I LFG, I usually get at least two responses within seconds.  My first couple of days there it was really hard to get a group.<br>
<br>
The other night, our group all bugged out so I went gated to Gfay to pickup bloodstones and such.  I decided to run over to mistmoore to see what was up since I had never been there before.  Got picked up by a group and we were pulling to the entrance.  Good xp there too and IMO better loot than in Loio.  From what I have read you don't want to try to solo there to hard to control the pull.  We always were adding familiars to our pulls.<br>
<br>
I hear there is a dude in a cell in HH Keep if you want to solo.  Guess he is good till about 30, from what I have read.  Never have tried him myself. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utaedirk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taedirk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/28/01 11:53:47 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LVL 24 wiz sick of killing birds</span><hr size=1> For soloing, right outside the sarnak fort in Lake of Ill Omen works for me at 26.  Bind near the Firiona Vie zone, not many people can make a train go that far and no roamers =).  Run along with the river and when you get to a very large body of water, the lake (well duh), go right along the shoreline.  Follow it until you see a line of pillars jutting out of the water.  Higher level druids, rangers, and the such usually quad bloodgills here, but they're stuck on the druid.  Bum a sow or just use root.  Anywhere around those pillars is good (until you get idiots PLers on one side, a warrior with a fungi tunic soloing on the other, and a 32 bard that doesn't realise he needs to leave omen in your pull area) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cumdar>Cumdar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/29/01 5:08:06 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LVL 24 wiz sick of killing birds</span><hr size=1> I've solo'ed by the lake as well.  I find that if you bind near the Frontier Mountain zone, you are actually closer to the area with the pillars.  Not to mention that you are closer to the Fort if you can find a group there and if you go to FM to fight giants, you are closer to there as well.  I think it is more centrally located to the fighting spots than the FV zone line.  You may want to try it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uorsmoxlorr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Orsmo Xlorr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/29/01 5:37:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> lvl 24</span><hr size=1> I would have to agree with the suggestions that were given here.  I did both the lake and Mistmoore at the level.  Mistmoore is a bit of a trick though if you are going to solo.<br>
<br>
The lake you can solo by the windmill.  lot's of mobs and fairly quick spawns.<br>
<br>
As for mistmoore the thing that makes it tricky is when those dang casters spawn in the zone in area.  What makes them hard is they are dam wizards and blast hard so keep the stun spell memmed.  Just use the zoneline and if someone else shouts train be ready to zone out.  Nothing see through invis near the zoneline but at night vampires will spawn farther in and if someone trains them to the zoneline they will whack ya.  Being a solo'er, because of limited play time, I used this zone for the extra dungeon bonus and leveled to 27 from 24 on just the &quot;yard trash&quot;.<br>
<br>
Orsmo Xlorr<br>
40 lvl Wizard <br>
Prexus<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unextonex.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nextonex</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/29/01 6:37:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: lvl 24</span><hr size=1> At 24 I was quadkiting the 4 goblin spawn between the windmill and the sarnak fort (back door I think). <br>
<br>
There are some nice posts on how to do it if you look around in the AE Kiting section. I was making 2 blue bubs a pull and went from 24 to 29 in 2 days! I don't think I'll ever XP solo like that again, but man it rocked! <p>Nextonex Atomsmasher of Prexus

Always looking for a good AOE group- send me a tell!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uellocopato.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ellocopato</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/29/01 6:44:42 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: lvl 24</span><hr size=1> Warsilik Woods Giant fort.  Great experience.   It's a root &amp; shoot soloing type.<br>
\ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukazzap.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kazzap</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/29/01 9:08:39 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: lvl 24</span><hr size=1> You might try EK?  Seems like I was getting good exp there on crag spiders, but that may have been a different level.<br>
<br>
Also, try giant skellies in Rathe Mtns <p>Kazzap Allahandra 54 Wizard<BR>
Iskendar Woundtempest 52 Warrior<BR>
<image src="http://kazzap.homestead.com/files/xegonytaxi2.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujjakajuan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JJakaJuan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/13/01 7:47:04 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hermit in SK BEST EXP 24-27</span><hr size=1> I can't believe no one put down the hermit spawn!!! Go to South Karana shout for the loc of the hermit. The hermit is a 2 minute spawn that can be easily killed! Once you find the hut look between the crack in the door to target him. Run behind the chimney then begin casting. You should get at least 3 nukes off before he runs out to you. Even so he does not hit hard and you have to be a really bad wizard to die to him. Loot is ok too, drops Fine steel occasionally. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cumdar>Cumdar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/14/01 9:21:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hermit in SK BEST EXP 24-27</span><hr size=1> Only problem with hermit is that it is always camped.  At least he is on Mith-Marr.  Usually by a stupid group too.  Ugh! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usvelna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>svelna</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/14/01 11:44:09 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LVL 24 wiz sick of killing birds</span><hr size=1> I did the bard @ the Nk spires.  Easy solable and great xp ... It jsut ruins your bard and qeynos factions but great xp and they are easy to fix<br>
<br>
Nerachnia<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cumdar>Cumdar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/16/01 5:23:03 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LVL 24 wiz sick of killing birds</span><hr size=1> Here is where not to solo:<br>
<br>
If your at kurn's tower camping the icy soloist wand, but your not finding enough Icebones, don't decide to drop down one of the pits and see if there is a place with more ice bones.  Jumped by 6 mobs.  Died two more times recovering my corpes.<br>
<br>
Don't go to Permafrost looking for a heart of frost and wander around with your invis up, then stumble across the Wizard who see's you first and has a friend.<br>
<br>
Don't go to Runnyeye to check out the changes and decide to attack this blue con sporali defender who appears to be alone.  4 more came out of no where and smoked me.<br>
<br>
6 deaths in 3 days.  Yuck.  Hadn't died in about 2 months.<br>
